<headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 31 at 6:37PM EDT  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...A BAND OF SNOW SHOWERS WITH LOW VISIBILITY DURING THE EARLY
EVENING...
WEATHER...
* A band of snow showers extending from Jackson to Toledo moves
eastward toward Monroe, the Detroit metro area, to near the
M-59 corridor during the late portion of the evening commute.
* Rapid reduction of visibility frequently to around a half mile
and briefly near a quarter mile is expected with the heavier
snow showers. Minor accumulation is also possible mainly on
objects and unpaved surfaces.
IMPACTS...
* Rapid fluctuation in driving visibility with wet roads will
require extra caution.
&amp;&amp;
PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
* Motorists are urged to use caution and account for the
variable driving conditions by allowing extra time.
* Prepare, plan and stay informed. Visit http://go.usa.gov/c7kkP</description>
